   Training

    Coping with Bioterrorism - The Role of the Laboratorian
     On University of North Carolina School of Public Health Web site
    Response to Bioterrorism  Part 1: Overview and Clinical Aspects of
     Critical Biological Agents
     RealPlayer video (1 hour 35 minutes) Requires the RealPlayer plugin
    Response to Bioterrorism  Part 2: The Laboratory Response Network
     and Agents of Bioterrorism
     RealPlayer video (1 hour 8 minutes) Requires the RealPlayer plugin
    National Laboratory Training Network (NLTN)
     Provides clinical, environmental, and public health laboratory training
     courses. Site includes extensive bioterrorism resources
    Centers for Public Health Preparedness
     Helps local public health workers prepare to respond to health threats,
     including bioterrorism
   Laboratory Response Network

   

     The Laboratory Response Network for Bioterrorism (LRN)
     Slide set. Describes responsibilities of each type of laboratory, how
     to access the State Public Health Laboratory, the Centers for Disease
     Control and Prevention, and the FBI to refer or report suspected
     agents.
     Adobe Acrobat Reader Adobe Acrobat Reader (771 KB)
